cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.DB, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geo-distributed data analysis in a cloud-edge system and proposes an algorithm for efficient execution of tasks across clusters.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for job acceleration in big data analytics systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with resource allocation and optimization in a distributed system.
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with data analysis and management in a distributed system.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper deals with wide area data transfer and cluster selection for efficient execution.
